			<ns0:name>krasin@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/krasin@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">It's not uncommon to have two or more NaCl modules running on the same machine from the same user. It does not make sense to waste the memory for loaded shared memory objects twice. In fact, it kills the idea of shared objects.

We need to mmap files instead of copying it to shm.
Of course, jit will still require shm segment. No problem here.

This feature will significantly reduce memory consumption if more than one NaCl module is loaded.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-25T00:06:51.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-06-14T20:08:44.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Available</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
